Interface I_cybernetic_thing

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    A_Animal, A_Container, A_Mammal, A_Mammal0, A_NDS, A_VisibleAgent, C_Background, C_BurrowSystem, C_City, C_Crop, C_Egg, C_HumanCarrier, C_HumanCarrier_OriginDestinationTransport, C_LandPlot, C_Region, C_Rodent, C_RodentCaged, C_RodentCMR, C_RodentCommensal, C_RodentCommensalSimplified, C_RodentDomestic, C_RodentFossorial, C_SoilCell, C_SoilCellGraphed, C_SupportedContainer, C_Trap, C_Vehicle, C_Vehicle_OriginDestinationTransport

    public interface I_cybernetic_thing
    Any thing that takes input and produces actions is an Agent. Agents usually map input to output, but they may just produce outputs and ignore their inputs.
